title: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026

title: Chengdu Rongcheng FC vs Gangwon FC (KOR) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD2
title_en_trans: Chengdu Rongcheng FC vs Gangwon FC (KOR) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD2
synopsis: Chengdu Rongcheng will face Gangwon for the first time in AFC Champions League Elite; each of the last three games in the competition between teams from Korea and China have been won by the former by an exact 2-1 score, including Gangwon’s win over Shanghai Shenhua in the first round of the 2025-26 season. Gangwon beat Shanghai Shenhua 2-1 in their first ever AFC Champions League Elite game at home; the last Korean side to suffer at least one defeat in their first two games in the competition is Jeju United in 2011, while no side from Korea has suffered defeat in their first away game in the AFC Champions League Elite.

synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

synopsis: Johor Darul Ta’zim will be playing against Machida Zelvia for the first time in AFC Champions League history; Johor Darul Ta’zim are winless in their last seven games in the competition against teams from Japan, failing to score in each of the last five of these games. title: Valentin Vacherot (MON) vs Arthur Rinderknech (FRA) - Final - Rolex Shanghai Masters ATP 1000
title_en_trans: Valentin Vacherot (MON) vs Arthur Rinderknech (FRA) - Final - Rolex Shanghai Masters ATP 1000
synopsis: Valentin Vacherot (MON) vs Arthur Rinderknech (FRA). First cousins meet in a historic Masters final after shock runs—qualifier Vacherot beat Djokovic; Rinderknech upset Medvedev to reach his first Masters title match. A family affair with big serves and fearless baseline hitting—expect tight sets and high drama in Shanghai.

title: Cesson-Rennes vs Montpellier - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Cesson-Rennes vs Montpellier - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: DTM  Show 2025-Red Bull Ring Part 1
synopsis: DTM. The embodiment of Motorsport tradition. Having just turned 40, the DTM combines a unique fascination and familiarity with an unmistakable dynamic, signified by the rebranding with a new logo! Seven different manufacturers – ten different winners on six brands (Audi, BMW, Mercedes, Lamborghini, Porsche and Ferrari) through twelve races are but one testament to the unique competitive balance that makes every DTM weekend a revelation! And with the addition of Ford, the palette of different brands is only increasing!

title: Le Havre vs Rennes - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Le Havre vs Rennes - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Le Havre have lost four of their last five home games against Rennes in Ligue 1, after only losing one of the first 16. Le Havre failed to score for the third time in Ligue 1 in 2025 in their last match at Metz ; only Lyon  and Paris SG  have failed to score in fewer matches in the competition this calendar year among ever present teams. It was also Le Havre’s second clean sheet of the year, the lowest tally amongst all teams in Ligue 1.

synopsis: Leeds United have lost nine of their last 11 Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, including each of their last four in a row – their longest ever league losing run to Spurs. title: My Faith in Sport - Ummah
synopsis:
Ummah is an Arabic word meaning "community” – an important concept in Islam as it encourages Muslims to support and help each other especially in times of need. Zakat is one of the most important aspects in Islam - it is the principle of giving back to a community/person that needs it more than you. 
This episode will look into Zakat around footballers Ali-Al Hamadi and Nadia Nadim and the role it plays in their lives. Al-Hamadi is the first Iraqi to play in the Premier League with a remarkable back story – his family escaped persecution in their homeland in the early 2000s before settling, as refugees, in Liverpool. title: Race 4 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: The Misano finale. Championship hopefuls chase maximum points as fatigue, tyre life and track limits shape the last attacks. Anticipate safety-car drama, photo-finish drafts to the stripe, and decisive moves under pressure as the round closes with a flat-out sprint.

title: DTM  Show 2025-Red Bull Ring Part 2
synopsis: DTM. The embodiment of Motorsport tradition. Having just turned 40, the DTM combines a unique fascination and familiarity with an unmistakable dynamic, signified by the rebranding with a new logo! Seven different manufacturers – ten different winners on six brands (Audi, BMW, Mercedes, Lamborghini, Porsche and Ferrari) through twelve races are but one testament to the unique competitive balance that makes every DTM weekend a revelation! And with the addition of Ford, the palette of different brands is only increasing!

title: Tractor FC (IRN) vs Al Wahda FC (UAE) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD2
title_en_trans: Tractor FC (IRN) vs Al Wahda FC (UAE) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD2
synopsis: This will be the first ever AFC Champions League Elite fixture between Tractor and Al Wahda; Tractor are unbeaten in home games against sides from UAE in the competition, while Al Wahda are winless in away matches against sides from Iran in the tournament. Al Wahda won their opening game of an AFC Champions League Elite campaign for the first time since 2007, beating Al-Ittihad 2-1 on the opening matchday of the 2025-26 season; the only other time they won their first two matches of an AFC Champions League Elite campaign was also in 2007.

title_en_trans: Delfina Brea Senesi (ARG) / Gemma Triay Pons (ESP) vs  Ariana Sanchez Fallada (ESP) / Paula Josemari
synopsis: World No.1 pairing Gemma Triay/Delfina Brea face No.2 Ariana Sánchez/Paula Josemaría at Rotterdam Ahoy. A classic rivalry: Triay/Brea lead the season with multiple titles, including Germany P2 last week, while Sánchez/Josemaría chase revenge after losing six of seven meetings this year. title: Paris FC vs Lorient - Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Paris FC vs Lorient - Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Paris FC beat Lorient 3-2 in March 2025  after failing to win any of their first seven meetings in all competitions against them this century. synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Chelsea vs Benfica - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs Benfica - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
synopsis: Chelsea have won all four of their competitive meetings with Benfica, with the most recent of those coming earlier this year at the FIFA Club World Cup. This will be the first meeting between Chelsea and Benfica in the group/league phase of a competition, with the previous four all having come in the knockout stages: UEFA Champions League quarter-finals in 2011-12, UEFA Europa League final in 2012-13 and the FIFA Club World Cup last 16 earlier this year.

title: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
title_en_trans: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
synopsis: WorldSBK heads to Estoril for the weekend’s decisive Race 2. The long front straight and technical infield reward grip and bravery, with braking into Parabólica and the drag to Turn 1 often settling it. Expect drafting trains, tyre-management gambles, and late lunges as title hopes to tighten in a full-throttle finale.

synopsis: Everton have lost just one of their last 21 Premier League meetings with Crystal Palace, a 1-3 defeat in December 2021. Indeed, among all sides they have faced 20+ times in the competition, their points-per-game rate of 1.81 against the Eagles is bettered only against West Brom. Crystal Palace are winless in each of their last 10 Premier League away games against Everton  since a 3-2 victory in September 2014 under Neil Warnock.

title: Al Zawraa SC (IRQ) vs Al Nassr Club (KSA) - AFC Champions League Two 2025/2026 - West MD2 - Mini Mat
title_en_trans: Al Zawraa SC (IRQ) vs Al Nassr Club (KSA) - AFC Champions League Two 2025/2026 - West MD2 - Mini Mat
synopsis:
The AFC Champions League Two is the second-tier competition of Asian club football, ranked below the AFC Champions League Elite. 
Participation in the competition is open to clubs from the top 12 nations in the East and the West region based on the AFC club competitions ranking.
All games are live and exclusive only on beIN.

title: North. Ireland vs Germany - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
title_en_trans: North. Ireland vs Germany - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
synopsis: Northern Ireland are winless in their last 13 matches against Germany, losing the last 10 in a row. They last beat them back in November 1983 in a European Championship qualifier. Germany have won seven of their nine away matches against Northern Ireland, winning the last five in a row and scoring 15 goals in the process. Their most recent visit was a 2-0 win in September 2019 in a European Championship qualifier.

title: Wales vs Belgium - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
title_en_trans: Wales vs Belgium - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
synopsis: Wales are winless in five games against Belgium  since winning 3-1 against them at EURO 2016 in the quarter-finals. Belgium have won six of their nine World Cup qualifying matches against Wales  – their only defeat came in March 1993, losing 2-0 at Cardiff Arms Park.

title: Al Rayyan vs Al Gharafa - Qatar Stars League 2025/26 - W6
title_en_trans: Al Rayyan vs Al Gharafa - Qatar Stars League 2025/26 - W6
synopsis: The Qatari League is the official football league in Qatar. The league includes 12 teams. The most famous participating clubs are Al-Sadd, the champions of the last season; Al-Rayyan and Al-Arabi, the popular teams, Al-Duhail and Al-Gharafa, serious contenders for the title every season. The Qatari league includes star names such as Firmino, Verratti, and Qatari Akram Afif, the best player in Asia.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Reilly OPELKA (USA) vs Benjamin BONZI (FRA) -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
title_en_trans: Reilly OPELKA (USA) vs Benjamin BONZI (FRA) -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: History of the Asian Games
synopsis: From its beginnings to today, the Asian Games torch lighting has become a dazzling showcase of creativity and technology. Each edition brings fresh innovation, with Doha 2006’s unforgettable horse-and-rider moment still hailed as a highlight. As the 2026 Games in Japan draw near, excitement builds over what new spectacle will capture the world’s imagination.

title: Vissel Kobe (JPN) vs Melbourne City FC (AUS) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD2
title_en_trans: Vissel Kobe (JPN) vs Melbourne City FC (AUS) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD2
synopsis: This will be the first AFC Champions League Elite fixture between Vissel Kobe and Melbourne City; City are without a win in any of their three Champions League Elite games against Japanese sides, while Kobe have won their only previous game against an Australian opposition in the competition. Vissel Kobe won their last AFC Champions League Elite game against Shanghai Port by a 3-0 margin; however, they have not won consecutive games in the competition since their three-match winning run between October and November 2024.

title: Scotland vs Belarus - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
title_en_trans: Scotland vs Belarus - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
synopsis: Scotland have won three of their previous five meetings with Belarus, with each of those coming in World Cup qualifying – the most recent was just last month, with the Scots winning 2-0 in Belarus. This will be Belarus’ third trip to face Scotland, losing the first 4-1 in September 1997 before winning the most recent 1-0 in October 2005.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. synopsis: This will be the first AFC Champions League Elite fixture between Vissel Kobe and Melbourne City; City are without a win in any of their three Champions League Elite games against Japanese sides, while Kobe have won their only previous game against an Australian opposition in the competition. synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: M2 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Shanghai Shenhua FC (CHN) vs Ulsan HD FC (KOR) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD2
title_en_trans: Shanghai Shenhua FC (CHN) vs Ulsan HD FC (KOR) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD2
synopsis: Ulsan HD have won each of their three AFC Champions League Elite games against Shanghai Shenhua, scoring at least two goals in each of those games; in fact, they have won seven of their last eight such fixtures against Chinese teams, with their only defeat in that period being a 1-3 loss to Shanghai Port on 26 November 2024. Shanghai Shenhua have failed to score two or more goals in each of their last three AFC Champions League Elite fixtures, the last time they went on a longer such run was a stretch of six games between April 2009 and April 2011.

title: M3 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: My Faith in Sport - Sawm
synopsis: Ramadan is a crucial period in the Islamic calendar but fasting (Sawm) can provide complications for athletes who are trying to compete at the highest level. But to what extent is fasting a negative or can it actually aid performance? We look at the life and adaptation throughout Ramadan of Adam Azim – an unbeaten professional boxer from the UK, Fares El Bakh – a weightlifter who won Qatar’s first ever Olympic gold medal, and Zainab Alema – a rugby player who is aiming to become the first player to represent England wearing a hijab. Experts in Sports Science and Nutrition from Aspetar Clinic, Qatar also add detail of the physical impact athletes encounter during Ramadan.

synopsis: Top seeds Arturo Coello/Agustín Tapia clash with No.2 Alejandro Galán/Federico Chingotto. Coello/Tapia dominated most of 2025, but Galán/Chingotto struck back with victory in Germany P2. Head-to-head favors Coello/Tapia, yet momentum is split after recent meetings. Indoor conditions at Rotterdam Ahoy amplify aggressive volleys and x-3 smashes, setting up a high-stakes P1 decider.

synopsis: Brest have won five of their last six matches against Nantes in all competitions, just one fewer than in their first 34 competitive clashes with FCN. title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Nîmes vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Nîmes vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Aston Villa vs Burnley - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Aston Villa vs Burnley - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Aston Villa have won both of their last two Premier League games against Burnley but haven’t won more successive league meetings with the Clarets since March 1900. Burnley’s last league visit to Aston Villa saw them lose 3-2 in December 2023; they last lost successive away league matches at Villa in April 1966.

title: Delfina Brea Senesi (ARG) / Gemma Triay Pons (ESP) vs  Ariana Sanchez Fallada (ESP) / Paula Josemari
title_en_trans: Delfina Brea Senesi (ARG) / Gemma Triay Pons (ESP) vs  Ariana Sanchez Fallada (ESP) / Paula Josemari
synopsis: World No.1 pairing Gemma Triay/Delfina Brea face No.2 Ariana Sánchez/Paula Josemaría at Rotterdam Ahoy. A classic rivalry: Triay/Brea lead the season with multiple titles, including Germany P2 last week, while Sánchez/Josemaría chase revenge after losing six of seven meetings this year. Expect sharp returns, low volleys, and golden-point pressure in a battle for supremacy.

title: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
title_en_trans: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
synopsis: WorldSBK heads to Estoril for the weekend’s decisive Race 2. The long front straight and technical infield reward grip and bravery, with braking into Parabólica and the drag to Turn 1 often settling it. Expect drafting trains, tyre-management gambles, and late lunges as title hopes to tighten in a full-throttle finale.

It was also Le Havre’s second clean sheet of the year, the lowest tally amongst all teams in Ligue 1.

title: M2 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. title: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Leeds United have lost nine of their last 11 Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, including each of their last four in a row – their longest ever league losing run to Spurs. Tottenham have won both of their last two league visits to Elland Road and could beat Leeds United away from home three times running in the league for the very first time.

title: Wales vs Belgium - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8

synopsis: Wales are winless in five games against Belgium  since winning 3-1 against them at EURO 2016 in the quarter-finals. Belgium have won six of their nine World Cup qualifying matches against Wales  – their only defeat came in March 1993, losing 2-0 at Cardiff Arms Park.

synopsis: The Qatari League is the official football league in Qatar. The league includes 12 teams. The most famous participating clubs are Al-Sadd, the champions of the last season; Al-Rayyan and Al-Arabi, the popular teams, Al-Duhail and Al-Gharafa, serious contenders for the title every season. The Qatari league includes star names such as Firmino, Verratti, and Qatari Akram Afif, the best player in Asia.

Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Nîmes vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Nîmes vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Valentin Vacherot (MON) vs Arthur Rinderknech (FRA) - Final - Rolex Shanghai Masters ATP 1000
title_en_trans: Valentin Vacherot (MON) vs Arthur Rinderknech (FRA) - Final - Rolex Shanghai Masters ATP 1000
synopsis: Valentin Vacherot (MON) vs Arthur Rinderknech (FRA). First cousins meet in a historic Masters final after shock runs—qualifier Vacherot beat Djokovic; Rinderknech upset Medvedev to reach his first Masters title match. A family affair with big serves and fearless baseline hitting—expect tight sets and high drama in Shanghai.

title: Al Sadd SC (QAT) vs Sharjah FC (UAE) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD2
title_en_trans: Al Sadd SC (QAT) vs Sharjah FC (UAE) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD2
synopsis: Al Sadd are unbeaten in each of their previous two meetings with Sharjah in the AFC Champions League Elite, while keeping a clean sheet in both of those games; in fact, Al Sadd are unbeaten in each of their last 16 games against sides from UAE  in the competition.  Sharjah have conceded multiple goals in each of their last three games in the AFC Champions League Elite, including their opening game of the ongoing edition ; if they concede multiple goals in this game, they will equal their longest such run in the competition.

title: Race 1 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: The Misano weekend opens with a sprint that rewards clean starts, tyre warm-up and bravery through Curvone. Expect late dives into Turn 1, heavy braking at Quercia and traction duels out of Tramonto onto the back straight. Safety cars and track-limits calls can flip the order, while newcomers hunt points and title hopefuls set the tone for the round.

title: Race 2 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: Race 2 reshuffles the deck after overnight tweaks. Warmer track temps raise tyre-degradation stakes, making slipstream timing on the main straight vital. Inside lines at Turn 1 and measured exits from Tramonto decide most passes. Watch for undercuts on out-laps, safety-car restarts, and penalties for track limits as contenders bank crucial mid-round points.

title: Race 3 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: With setups refined, Race 3 is often the weekend’s fiercest sprint. Nose-to-tail packs form into Turn 1, while rhythm and patience through the fast right-lefts keep front tyres alive. Curvone commitment and a tidy run to Quercia create overtaking chances. Expect bold moves, defensive elbows, and strategy on push laps to climb

title: Saint-Raphaël vs Nîmes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Saint-Raphaël vs Nîmes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Al Ittihad Club (KSA) vs Shabab Al Ahli (UAE) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD2
title_en_trans: Al Ittihad Club (KSA) vs Shabab Al Ahli (UAE) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD2
synopsis: This will be the first meeting between Al-Ittihad and Shabab Al Ahli in AFC Champions League Elite history; teams from Saudi Arabia have won seven of their last eight games in the competition against teams from UAE, however, the one loss in this run was Al-Ittihad’s 1-2 loss to Al Wahda in their opening matchday of the 2025-26 season. Al-Ittihad have lost each of their last three AFC Champions League Elite games, their joint-longest run of such games in the competition, including a 1-2 loss to Al Wahda on Matchday 1; Al-Ittihad have never lost each of their first two games of an AFC Champions League Elite campaign and only twice have they failed to win any of their first two games.

title: M2 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

synopsis: World No.1 pairing Gemma Triay/Delfina Brea face No.2 Ariana Sánchez/Paula Josemaría at Rotterdam Ahoy. A classic rivalry: Triay/Brea lead the season with multiple titles, including Germany P2 last week, while Sánchez/Josemaría chase revenge after losing six of seven meetings this year. Expect sharp returns, low volleys, and golden-point pressure in a battle for supremacy.

title: Gold Standard Ep3
synopsis:
"The Clash of Titans" – Croatia 2009
In 2009, France defeated Croatia in Zagreb to secure their third world title. 
This episode focuses on the iconic duel between Karabatić and Balić, as well as Claude Onesta’s tactical genius that defined the “Experts” era.

title: Race 5 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: Rising talents go wheel-to-wheel at Misano World Circuit Marco Simoncelli in Race 5. Slipstreams on the main straight and commitment through Curvone shape the order, while track limits, safety cars, and bold restarts can flip everything late. A flat-out sprint where newcomers and title hopefuls fight to the flag.

title: M3-ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
title_en_trans: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
synopsis: WorldSBK heads to Estoril for the weekend’s decisive Race 2. The long front straight and technical infield reward grip and bravery, with braking into Parabólica and the drag to Turn 1 often settling it. Expect drafting trains, tyre-management gambles, and late lunges as title hopes to tighten in a full-throttle finale.

title: Race 1 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: The Misano weekend opens with a sprint that rewards clean starts, tyre warm-up and bravery through Curvone. Expect late dives into Turn 1, heavy braking at Quercia and traction duels out of Tramonto onto the back straight. Safety cars and track-limits calls can flip the order, while newcomers hunt points and title hopefuls set the tone for the round.

title: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Lille have won just one of their last 13 home Ligue 1 games against Paris SG, a 5-1 victory on 14 April 2019, which remains Paris Saint-Germain's biggest away defeat in the top-flight in the 21st century. Lille have lost their last two Ligue 1 matches and could suffer three consecutive defeats in the competition for the first time since December 2019-January 2020. Lille could also fail to score in three consecutive Ligue 1 games for the first time since September 2017.

synopsis: FC Seoul are unbeaten in each of their four meetings against Buriram United in the AFC Champions League Elite, including wins in each of their last two; in fact, FC Seoul have lost just one of their six meetings against Thai sides in the competition, with the loss coming in their most recent such game. Buriram United are unbeaten in each of their last five games in the AFC Champions League Elite against sides from South Korea ; their last loss against such a side came in May 2018.

title: Race 1 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: The Misano weekend opens with a sprint that rewards clean starts, tyre warm-up and bravery through Curvone. Expect late dives into Turn 1, heavy braking at Quercia and traction duels out of Tramonto onto the back straight. Safety cars and track-limits calls can flip the order, while newcomers hunt points and title hopefuls set the tone for the round.

title: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Lille have won just one of their last 13 home Ligue 1 games against Paris SG, a 5-1 victory on 14 April 2019, which remains Paris Saint-Germain's biggest away defeat in the top-flight in the 21st century. Lille have lost their last two Ligue 1 matches and could suffer three consecutive defeats in the competition for the first time since December 2019-January 2020. Lille could also fail to score in three consecutive Ligue 1 games for the first time since September 2017.

synopsis: Race 2 reshuffles the deck after overnight tweaks. Warmer track temps raise tyre-degradation stakes, making slipstream timing on the main straight vital. Inside lines at Turn 1 and measured exits from Tramonto decide most passes. Watch for undercuts on out-laps, safety-car restarts, and penalties for track limits as contenders bank crucial mid-round points.

title: Wales vs Belgium - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
title_en_trans: Wales vs Belgium - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
synopsis: Wales are winless in five games against Belgium  since winning 3-1 against them at EURO 2016 in the quarter-finals. Belgium have won six of their nine World Cup qualifying matches against Wales  – their only defeat came in March 1993, losing 2-0 at Cardiff Arms Park.

synopsis: The decisive GCL Team Round 2. Reverse-order start from Round 1, with every rail and second counting toward the combined team total. Strategic rider swaps and cool heads over a technical track shape the podium and precious championship points in a high-stakes Roman finish.

title: Race 3 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: With setups refined, Race 3 is often the weekend’s fiercest sprint. Nose-to-tail packs form into Turn 1, while rhythm and patience through the fast right-lefts keep front tyres alive. Curvone commitment and a tidy run to Quercia create overtaking chances. Expect bold moves, defensive elbows, and strategy on push laps to climb

title: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Leeds United have lost nine of their last 11 Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, including each of their last four in a row – their longest ever league losing run to Spurs. Tottenham have won both of their last two league visits to Elland Road and could beat Leeds United away from home three times running in the league for the very first time.

title_en_trans: Latvia vs England - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
synopsis: This will be the second meeting between Latvia and England, with the first coming in March this year when the Three Lions won 3-0 at Wembley with goals from Reece James, Harry Kane and Eberechi Eze. Latvia will be the 72nd nation England have played an away match against – they’ve won their last three first time away games against a nation.

title: Race 4 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: The Misano finale. Championship hopefuls chase maximum points as fatigue, tyre life and track limits shape the last attacks. A strong launch, disciplined braking at Quercia and perfect traction from Tramonto decide podiums. Anticipate safety-car drama, photo-finish drafts to the stripe, and decisive moves under pressure as the round closes with a flat-out sprint.

title: My Faith in Sport - Salah
synopsis: Exploring the importance of prayer within Islam, the episode begins with an overview of our seven athletes as they introduce themselves and why Islam is so important to them. We are also introduced to Omar Sulieman, a notable Imam, who acts as narration throughout the series and a guiding voice on the key principles of Islam. The life and career of Sofyan Amrabat is explored, showcasing his role as a key part of the Fenerbahce team in Turkey and the Moroccan national side. The Atlas Lions’ run to the semi-finals of the FIFA World Cup Qatar 2022 is explored, with the impact that Salah played in the team’s belief and positivity throughout the tournament.

The Atlas Lions’ run to the semi-finals of the FIFA World Cup Qatar 2022 is explored, with the impact that Salah played in the team’s belief and positivity throughout the tournament.

synopsis: Chelsea have won all four of their competitive meetings with Benfica, with the most recent of those coming earlier this year at the FIFA Club World Cup. This will be the first meeting between Chelsea and Benfica in the group/league phase of a competition, with the previous four all having come in the knockout stages: UEFA Champions League quarter-finals in 2011-12, UEFA Europa League final in 2012-13 and the FIFA Club World Cup last 16 earlier this year.

title: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
title_en_trans: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
synopsis: WorldSBK heads to Estoril for the weekend’s decisive Race 2. The long front straight and technical infield reward grip and bravery, with braking into Parabólica and the drag to Turn 1 often settling it. Expect drafting trains, tyre-management gambles, and late lunges as title hopes to tighten in a full-throttle finale.

title: My Faith in Sport - Taffakur
synopsis: Islam teaches Muslims about ‘Tawakkul’ meaning trusting in God’s plan. Muslims believe in the idea that with anything in life we put forward our best efforts but ultimately the rest is left to God and believing whatever the outcome, it was pre-written. Omar Marmoush is the feature athlete in the final episode of the series – from the outskirts of the Eintracht Frankfurt side to an $80m move to Premier League Manchester City, his last 18 months has seen an incredible rise. His love of Ramadan and belief that fasting elevates his game is a central theme of the final episode alongside detail of his early life, career and his unfaltering belief in Islam. The series concludes with all athletes re

title_en_trans: FC Seoul (KOR) vs Buriram United (THA) -AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD2
synopsis: FC Seoul are unbeaten in each of their four meetings against Buriram United in the AFC Champions League Elite, including wins in each of their last two; in fact, FC Seoul have lost just one of their six meetings against Thai sides in the competition, with the loss coming in their most recent such game. Buriram United are unbeaten in each of their last five games in the AFC Champions League Elite against sides from South Korea ; their last loss against such a side came in May 2018.

title: Melbourne City FC (AUS) vs Sanfrecce Hiroshima (JPN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East M
title_en_trans: Melbourne City FC (AUS) vs Sanfrecce Hiroshima (JPN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East M
synopsis: This will be the first-ever AFC Champions League Elite meeting between Melbourne City and Sanfrecce Hiroshima; City are winless in each of their two games against Japanese opposition in the competition, while a win for Sanfrecce would see them beat Australian opponents in three consecutive games for the first time in competition history. Melbourne City are winless in each of their last three matches in the AFC Champions League Elite, their longest such run in the competition; in fact, they have begun each of their previous two campaigns in the competition with draws.

title: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3
title_en_trans: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3
synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.
synopsis_en_trans:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
title_en_trans: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
synopsis: WorldSBK heads to Estoril for the weekend’s decisive Race 2. The long front straight and technical infield reward grip and bravery, with braking into Parabólica and the drag to Turn 1 often settling it. Expect drafting trains, tyre-management gambles, and late lunges as title hopes to tighten in a full-throttle finale.

title: Gangwon FC (KOR) vs Shanghai Shenhua FC (CHN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD1
title_en_trans: Gangwon FC (KOR) vs Shanghai Shenhua FC (CHN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD1
synopsis: This will be the first AFC Champions League Elite meeting between Gangwon and Shanghai Shenhua, with the former set to play their first-ever game in the competition; Shenhua have lost each of their last two matches against South Korean opposition in the Champions League Elite, another defeat here will see them equal their longest such run in competition history. Shanghai Shenhua lost their most recent AFC Champions League Elite match 0-4 to Kawasaki Frontale on 12 March 2025; failure to score against Gangwon will see them go scoreless in consecutive games for the first time in the competition since May 2011.

synopsis: Sevilla have not won any of their last 19 LaLiga games against Barcelona, a run that stretches back to October 2015, losing their last seven in a row – their longest consecutive losing streak against the Catalans in the top-flight. title: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
title_en_trans: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
synopsis: WorldSBK heads to Estoril for the weekend’s decisive Race 2. The long front straight and technical infield reward grip and bravery, with braking into Parabólica and the drag to Turn 1 often settling it. Expect drafting trains, tyre-management gambles, and late lunges as title hopes to tighten in a full-throttle finale.

title: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3
title_en_trans: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3
synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title: Aston Villa vs Burnley - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Aston Villa vs Burnley - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Aston Villa have won both of their last two Premier League games against Burnley but haven’t won more successive league meetings with the Clarets since March 1900. Burnley’s last league visit to Aston Villa saw them lose 3-2 in December 2023; they last lost successive away league matches at Villa in April 1966.

title: M4 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

synopsis: The Qatari League is the official football league in Qatar. The league includes 12 teams. The most famous participating clubs are Al-Sadd, the champions of the last season; Al-Rayyan and Al-Arabi, the popular teams, Al-Duhail and Al-Gharafa, serious contenders for the title every season. The Qatari league includes star names such as Firmino, Verratti, and Qatari Akram Afif, the best player in Asia.

synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

synopsis: WorldSBK heads to Estoril for the weekend’s decisive Race 2. The long front straight and technical infield reward grip and bravery, with braking into Parabólica and the drag to Turn 1 often settling it. synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title_en_trans: Al Wahda FC (UAE) vs Al Ittihad Club (KSA) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
synopsis: Al Wahda are unbeaten in each of their last three AFC Champions League Elite matches against Al-Ittihad, having lost each of their three meetings in the competition prior to then; in fact, Al Wahda have scored five times in their last two games against Al-Ittihad in the competition, after failing to score even one goal in the first four such meetings between the two sides. Al Wahda have failed to win any of their last seven opening games in the AFC Champions League Elite, last doing so in 2007 ; in fact, they have failed to score in each of their last three such matches in the competition.

title: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3
title_en_trans: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3
synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title: Race - Qiddiya Round - Extreme H World Cup 2025
title_en_trans: Race - Qiddiya Round - Extreme H World Cup 2025
synopsis: Extreme H World Cup hits Qiddiya for a desert race. Hydrogen-powered Pioneer 25 SUVs face Time Trials, head-to-head heats, and a multi-car Grand Final, with energy management, tyre wear and route choice deciding positions. Expect dunes, dust and daring passes under the Tuwaiq cliffs, driver switches, and strategy on boost usage as teams chase points, manufacturer bragging rights and momentum in the sport’s new zero-emissions era. Broadcast highlights and on-board shots bring the action home.

title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Leeds United have lost nine of their last 11 Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, including each of their last four in a row – their longest ever league losing run to Spurs. Tottenham have won both of their last two league visits to Elland Road and could beat Leeds United away from home three times running in the league for the very first time.

title: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025

synopsis: WorldSBK heads to Estoril for the weekend’s decisive Race 2. The long front straight and technical infield reward grip and bravery, with braking into Parabólica and the drag to Turn 1 often settling it. Expect drafting trains, tyre-management gambles, and late lunges as title hopes to tighten in a full-throttle finale.

title: My Faith in Sport - Ummah
synopsis:
Ummah is an Arabic word meaning "community” – an important concept in Islam as it encourages Muslims to support and help each other especially in times of need. Zakat is one of the most important aspects in Islam - it is the principle of giving back to a community/person that needs it more than you. 
This episode will look into Zakat around footballers Ali-Al Hamadi and Nadia Nadim and the role it plays in their lives. Al-Hamadi is the first Iraqi to play in the Premier League with a remarkable back story – his family escaped persecution in their homeland in the early 2000s before settling, as refugees, in Liverpool. title: M3 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title_en_trans: Latvia vs England - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
synopsis: This will be the second meeting between Latvia and England, with the first coming in March this year when the Three Lions won 3-0 at Wembley with goals from Reece James, Harry Kane and Eberechi Eze. Latvia will be the 72nd nation England have played an away match against – they’ve won their last three first time away games against a nation.

title: Nîmes vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Nîmes vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Race 1 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: The Misano weekend opens with a sprint that rewards clean starts, tyre warm-up and bravery through Curvone. Expect late dives into Turn 1, heavy braking at Quercia and traction duels out of Tramonto onto the back straight. Safety cars and track-limits calls can flip the order, while newcomers hunt points and title hopefuls set the tone for the round.

title: Race 2 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: Race 2 reshuffles the deck after overnight tweaks. Warmer track temps raise tyre-degradation stakes, making slipstream timing on the main straight vital. Inside lines at Turn 1 and measured exits from Tramonto decide most passes. Watch for undercuts on out-laps, safety-car restarts, and penalties for track limits as contenders bank crucial mid-round points.

title: M4 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Arsenal vs West Ham United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Arsenal vs West Ham United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Arsenal have lost both of their last two home league games against West Ham, only ever losing three in a row once before. West Ham United are looking to become only the second side to win three successive Premier League away games against Arsenal, after Manchester City, who won six on the bounce from March 2018 to February 2023.

title: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3
title_en_trans: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3
synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

Villarreal have lost 17 of their 25 LaLiga away matches against Real Madrid, their highest number of away defeats against a single opponent in the competition.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Race - Qiddiya Round - Extreme H World Cup 2025
title_en_trans: Race - Qiddiya Round - Extreme H World Cup 2025
synopsis: Extreme H World Cup hits Qiddiya for a desert race. Hydrogen-powered Pioneer 25 SUVs face Time Trials, head-to-head heats, and a multi-car Grand Final, with energy management, tyre wear and route choice deciding positions. Expect dunes, dust and daring passes under the Tuwaiq cliffs, driver switches, and strategy on boost usage as teams chase points, manufacturer bragging rights and momentum in the sport’s new zero-emissions era. Broadcast highlights and on-board shots bring the action home.

title_en_trans: Latvia vs England - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
synopsis: This will be the second meeting between Latvia and England, with the first coming in March this year when the Three Lions won 3-0 at Wembley with goals from Reece James, Harry Kane and Eberechi Eze. Latvia will be the 72nd nation England have played an away match against – they’ve won their last three first time away games against a nation.

synopsis: The 2025–26 UEFA Europa League is the secondary club football tournament organised by UEFA. This is the second season played under a new format, which replaced the 32-team group stage with a 36-team league phase. Tottenham Hotspur are the reigning champions. The final will be played on 20 May 2026 at Beşiktaş Stadium in Istanbul, Turkey.

title: Paris FC vs Lorient - Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Paris FC vs Lorient - Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Paris FC beat Lorient 3-2 in March 2025  after failing to win any of their first seven meetings in all competitions against them this century. Paris FC have conceded 13 goals in their six Ligue 1 matches this season, with only Lorient  conceding more; this is as many goals as Paris FC conceded in their final 12 Ligue 2 games last season.

title: M3 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Brentford vs Manchester City - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8

synopsis: Since completing a Premier League double over Manchester City in 2022-23, Brentford are winless in their last four against the Citizens in the division. title: Al Ahli Saudi FC (KSA) vs PFC Nasaf (UZB) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
title_en_trans: Al Ahli Saudi FC (KSA) vs PFC Nasaf (UZB) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
synopsis: This will be the fifth AFC Champions League Elite meeting between Al-Ahli and Nasaf, with Nasaf’s only win coming in their most recent such game on 2 March 2016 ; Al-Ahli’s most recent game in the competition against Uzbek opposition was a 2-1 win over Pakhtakor Tashkent on 20 May 2019, a win here will see them win two consecutive such games for the first time in competition history. Al-Ahli are unbeaten in each of their last 18 AFC Champions League Elite games, including the final of the 2024-25 edition ; avoiding defeat here will see them equal Gamba Osaka for the joint third-longest such run in the competition.

title: Everton vs Crystal Palace - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Everton vs Crystal Palace - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Everton have lost just one of their last 21 Premier League meetings with Crystal Palace, a 1-3 defeat in December 2021. Indeed, among all sides they have faced 20+ times in the competition, their points-per-game rate of 1.81 against the Eagles is bettered only against West Brom. Crystal Palace are winless in each of their last 10 Premier League away games against Everton  since a 3-2 victory in September 2014 under Neil Warnock.

Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. synopsis: This will be the first ever AFC Champions League Elite meeting between Al Shorta and Al Sadd; Iraqi teams have won five of their last seven matches against Qatari sides in the competition, after winning just one of the first seven. Al Shorta failed to win any of their first three matches against Qatari teams in the competition  and did not score in those games, but they won their last such meeting 2-1 vs Al Duhail in April 2021.

title: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3
title_en_trans: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3
synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026

synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: M3 - ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

synopsis: The 2025–26 UEFA Europa League is the secondary club football tournament organised by UEFA. The final will be played on 20 May 2026 at Beşiktaş Stadium in Istanbul, Turkey.

title: Race 1 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: The Misano weekend opens with a sprint that rewards clean starts, tyre warm-up and bravery through Curvone. Expect late dives into Turn 1, heavy braking at Quercia and traction duels out of Tramonto onto the back straight. Safety cars and track-limits calls can flip the order, while newcomers hunt points and title hopefuls set the tone for the round.

title: AFC Awards Riyadh 2025
synopsis:
The biggest names from across Asia will celebrate a fantastic year of football.
The 29th edition of the annual gala ceremony will recognise the continent’s finest across a total of 20 categories, including the prestigious Male & Female AFC Player of the Year awards.
Hosted in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia for the first time, the event will be staged at the King Fahad Cultural Center, Riyadh.

title: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Lille have won just one of their last 13 home Ligue 1 games against Paris SG, a 5-1 victory on 14 April 2019, which remains Paris Saint-Germain's biggest away defeat in the top-flight in the 21st century. Lille have lost their last two Ligue 1 matches and could suffer three consecutive defeats in the competition for the first time since December 2019-January 2020. Lille could also fail to score in three consecutive Ligue 1 games for the first time since September 2017.

title: Race 2 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: Race 2 reshuffles the deck after overnight tweaks. Warmer track temps raise tyre-degradation stakes, making slipstream timing on the main straight vital. synopsis: Live and exclusive action from the EFL (English Football League) One. EFL One is the third-tier in the English football league system. synopsis: Leeds United have lost nine of their last 11 Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, including each of their last four in a row – their longest ever league losing run to Spurs. Tottenham have won both of their last two league visits to Elland Road and could beat Leeds United away from home three times running in the league for the very first time.

title: Race 4 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
synopsis: The Misano finale. Championship hopefuls chase maximum points as fatigue, tyre life and track limits shape the last attacks. A strong launch, disciplined braking at Quercia and perfect traction from Tramonto decide podiums. Anticipate safety-car drama, photo-finish drafts to the stripe, and decisive moves under pressure as the round closes with a flat-out sprint.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

synopsis:
"A Farewell to Legends" – France 2017
France’s 2017 victory on home soil was both a celebration and a goodbye to legends like Omeyer and Narcisse. 
This emotional win against Norway secured their sixth title and closed a golden chapter in French handball.

title: My Faith in Sport - Sawm
synopsis: Ramadan is a crucial period in the Islamic calendar but fasting (Sawm) can provide complications for athletes who are trying to compete at the highest level. But to what extent is fasting a negative or can it actually aid performance? We look at the life and adaptation throughout Ramadan of Adam Azim – an unbeaten professional boxer from the UK, Fares El Bakh – a weightlifter who won Qatar’s first ever Olympic gold medal, and Zainab Alema – a rugby player who is aiming to become the first player to represent England wearing a hijab. Experts in Sports Science and Nutrition from Aspetar Clinic, Qatar also add detail of the physical impact athletes encounter during Ramadan.

title: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Leeds United have lost nine of their last 11 Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, including each of their last four in a row – their longest ever league losing run to Spurs. Tottenham have won both of their last two league visits to Elland Road and could beat Leeds United away from home three times running in the league for the very first time.

title: Scotland vs Belarus - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
title_en_trans: Scotland vs Belarus - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
synopsis: Scotland have won three of their previous five meetings with Belarus, with each of those coming in World Cup qualifying – the most recent was just last month, with the Scots winning 2-0 in Belarus. This will be Belarus’ third trip to face Scotland, losing the first 4-1 in September 1997 before winning the most recent 1-0 in October 2005.

title: M3 - ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Al Hilal SFC (KSA) vs Al Duhail SC (QAT) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
title_en_trans: Al Hilal SFC (KSA) vs Al Duhail SC (QAT) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
synopsis: Al Duhail won their first AFC Champions League Elite meeting with Al-Hilal, but Al-Hilal are unbeaten in the six since, including their joint-biggest win in the competition  – Al Duhail’s heaviest defeat in the tournament. Qatari teams have lost their last five matches against Saudi sides in the competition; their last win was Al Sadd’s 2-1 victory over Al-Nassr in December 2014. Qatari teams have lost more matches  and conceded more goals  against Saudi teams than against any other nation.

title: Everton vs Crystal Palace - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Everton vs Crystal Palace - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Everton have lost just one of their last 21 Premier League meetings with Crystal Palace, a 1-3 defeat in December 2021. Indeed, among all sides they have faced 20+ times in the competition, their points-per-game rate of 1.81 against the Eagles is bettered only against West Brom. Crystal Palace are winless in each of their last 10 Premier League away games against Everton  since a 3-2 victory in September 2014 under Neil Warnock.

title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Wales vs Belgium - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
title_en_trans: Wales vs Belgium - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
synopsis: Wales are winless in five games against Belgium  since winning 3-1 against them at EURO 2016 in the quarter-finals. Belgium have won six of their nine World Cup qualifying matches against Wales  – their only defeat came in March 1993, losing 2-0 at Cardiff Arms Park.

title: Arturo Coello (ESP) / Agustin Tapia (ARG) vs  Federico Chingotto (ARG) / Alejandro Galan (ESP) - Men
title_en_trans: Arturo Coello (ESP) / Agustin Tapia (ARG) vs  Federico Chingotto (ARG) / Alejandro Galan (ESP) - Men
synopsis: Top seeds Arturo Coello/Agustín Tapia clash with No.2 Alejandro Galán/Federico Chingotto. Coello/Tapia dominated most of 2025, but Galán/Chingotto struck back with victory in Germany P2. Head-to-head favors Coello/Tapia, yet momentum is split after recent meetings. Indoor conditions at Rotterdam Ahoy amplify aggressive volleys and x-3 smashes, setting up a high-stakes P1 decider.

title_en_trans: Latvia vs England - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
synopsis: This will be the second meeting between Latvia and England, with the first coming in March this year when the Three Lions won 3-0 at Wembley with goals from Reece James, Harry Kane and Eberechi Eze. title: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3
title_en_trans: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3
synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title: M2 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

synopsis: Monaco will face OGC Nice for the 131st time in all competitions. Monaco have recorded 58 wins against OGC Nice, a figure they have only achieved against Lyon and Rennes. OGC Nice, in turn, have lost to Monaco 58 times in all competitions, with only defeats against Marseille  being more frequent. Monaco have lost three of their last five Ligue 1 matches against Nice, as many defeats as in their previous 12 encounters with OGCN.

title: M3 - ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Manchester United vs Sunderland - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Manchester United vs Sunderland - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Manchester United have lost just two of their last 30 league games against Sunderland, with this their first since a 3-0 win in April 2017. Across all competitions, Sunderland have managed to win just one of their last 31 away games against Manchester United, winning 1-0 in May 2014 thanks to Sebastian Larsson’s winner.

title: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3
title_en_trans: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3
synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: One Friday Fight -129
synopsis: ONE Friday Fights 129 lights up Bangkok on Oct 17 with 12 bouts across Muay Thai, MMA, and kickboxing. Expect fireworks in the headliner as Thailand’s Tengnueng collides with Myanmar’s Tun Min Aung in a KO-hungry showdown. Plus, standout clashes: Petlampun vs Ayad Albadr, and 19-year-old Fergus Smith vs Zahran Al-Wesabi. Live from Lumpinee Boxing Stadium, its elbows, knees, and spinning kicks all night in a stacked showcase. Prelims spotlight rising prospects; main card promises fast finishes.

title: Wolverhampton Wanderers vs Brighton & Hove Albion - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Wolverhampton Wanderers vs Brighton & Hove Albion - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Wolves have won just two of their 14 Premier League games against Brighton  and are winless in their last seven  since a 1-0 triumph in December 2021 under Bruno Lage. Brighton have won each of their last four league visits to Wolves; the only sides the Seagulls have ever won 5+ successive away games against in their league history are Grimsby Town  and Wolves themselves.

title: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Lille have won just one of their last 13 home Ligue 1 games against Paris SG, a 5-1 victory on 14 April 2019, which remains Paris Saint-Germain's biggest away defeat in the top-flight in the 21st century. Lille have lost their last two Ligue 1 matches and could suffer three consecutive defeats in the competition for the first time since December 2019-January 2020. Lille could also fail to score in three consecutive Ligue 1 games for the first time since September 2017.

title: M2 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

synopsis: The Qatari League is the official football league in Qatar. The league includes 12 teams. The most famous participating clubs are Al-Sadd, the champions of the last season; Al-Rayyan and Al-Arabi, the popular teams, Al-Duhail and Al-Gharafa, serious contenders for the title every season. The Qatari league includes star names such as Firmino, Verratti, and Qatari Akram Afif, the best player in Asia.

title: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: M3 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026

synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

synopsis: WorldSBK heads to Estoril for the weekend’s decisive Race 2. synopsis: Paris Saint-Germain are unbeaten in their 34 home games against Strasbourg in Ligue 1, the most home games by a team against another without losing in the history of the top-flight. Paris Saint-Germain have won three Ligue 1 matches by two or more goals this season, the joint-most with Marseille, though they have only done so fewer times after seven Ligue 1 matches in two previous seasons under QSI ownership.

title: M4 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
